56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.5c8c38d4-3569-4256-8501-1f48dface1e2.description=
Cette opération permet de déterminer le type d'action unitaire (via les Responses) en fonction du paramètre en input.

Inputs\:
--------------------------------
selectActionFlow \:	Action unitaire

Outputs\:
--------------------------------
N/A

Responses\:
--------------------------------
SP \: 		L'action unitaire correspond à une Software Policy HPSA
SC \: 		L'action unitaire correspond à un Script HPSA
FL \: 		L'action unitaire correspond à un flow HPOO
unknown \: 		L'action unitaire ne correspond à aucun des types ci-dessus

56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.a46634a6-7ac7-48bf-8b6f-7c1f8b9b918d.description=
Retrieves information about the status of a flow run given its runId. It also returns detailed information about the status of the steps. The flow run information is added as separate results to the operation and the steps status is formated as JSON array where each item contains information about a step status.

Inputs\:
    host - The host running the Central service.
Default value\: localhost.
    username - The username to use when connecting to the Central service.
    password - The password to use when connecting to the Central service.
    port - The port the Central service is running on.
Default value\: 8443.
    protocol - Either http or https. The protocol used to communicate to the Central service.
Default value\: https.
    trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false.
    trustKeystore - The path of the truststore file. It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used. If not specified  the operation will search for{iconclude_home}/Central/conf/rc_keystore or {iconclude_home}/Studio/conf/rc_keystore in this order.
    trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore. Provide this input only if trustKeystore is not empty.
    runId - The runId of the running flow.
    primaryResultWanted - If true, the operation will return the primary result of the flow run.
Default value\: false.
Valid values\: true, false.
    rawResultWanted - If true, the operation will return the raw result of the flow run.
Default value\: false.
Valid values\: true, false.

Returns\:
    returnResult - A message informing the user about the success or failure of the operation.
    status - The status of the flow run. Currently, the available values are\:Unknown, Running, Paused, EndedOrFinished, Canceled,
    cursorPosition -  Represents the current step index into run history.
    runReportUrl - Represents the report link URL to the run.
    runResponse -  Represents the response of the flow run.
    runResumeUrl - Represents the resume link URL to run if run is not finished.
    stepsStatus - A JSON array representation of the steps status. Each item of the array has the following properties\: 
        stepName -  The name of the step.
        startTime - Represents the start time of the step since 1/1/1970 00\:00am, in milliseconds.
        endTime - Represents the end time of the step since 1/1/1970 00\:00am, in milliseconds.
        stepResponse - The response of the step, based on the definition of the step.
        flowName -  Represents the name of the flow the step belongs to.
        stepLevel - Zero based integer that represents the step level in the flow run; each subflow run represents a level. So, if the client runs flowA which runs flowB which in turn runs flowC, the level of all the steps under flowC would be 3. Level zero is the flow itself.

Responses\:
    success -The operation retrieved the status of the running flow.
    failure - Could not connect to central web service. Invalid runId.

Note\:
Use the operations and flows from Library/Utility Operations/Containers/JSON to parse the stepsStatus result.
56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.b04f182f-6c4f-4a90-b2b5-6173d12da036.description=
Compares two dates. If the locale is not specified, the inputs must be in the format of date/time format of OO Central Server's, which is dependant of Java Locale. You can use flow " Get Current Date and Time" to check upon the default date/time format. If locale is specified, the inputs must be in the format of the locale. If locale is not specified, then default locale will be used.

Inputs\:
d1 - The first date. For example, if locale is not specified and the OS default locale is English, the format could be "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM" or "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM PST". If locale en is specified, the format should be "July 12, 2006 4\:23\:20 PM PST".
d2 - The second date.  It must be in the format that is the same as d1.
threshold -The number of milliseconds around each date that still allows the dates to be considered equal.
localeLang - The locale language for date and time string. For example,  en or ja.
localeCountry - The locale country for date and time string. For example, US or JP. If localeLang is not specified, this input will be ingored.

Responses\:
before - If d1 is before d2.
equal - If d1 is < d2 + threshold and d1 > d2-threshold.
after - If d1 is after d2.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
The value of d1-d2 in milliseconds.
56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.ccfa8310-d591-4af7-ae65-0ebb4ae2167f.description=
Check the current date and time, and returns a java DateAndTime formatted string of it. If locale is specified, it will return the date and time string based on the locale.Otherwise, default locale will be used.

Inputs\:
localeLang - The locale language for date and time string. For example,  en or ja.
localeCountry - The locale country for date and time string. For example, US or JP. If localeLang is not specified, this input will be ingored.

Result\:
Current date and time.

Responses\:
success - Date/time retrieved successfully.
failure - Date/time could not be retrieved.

56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.de0d60e7-9f13-4b91-8722-a2cb562c5486.description=
Offsets the current date and time by a given number of units. If locale is specified, the date and time will be in the format based on the locale. Otherwise, default locale will be used. 

Inputs\:
units - The number of units to offset by. If this is positive, the offset goes into the future, if it is negative the offset goes into the past.
secondsPerUnit - The number of seconds per unit. This defaults to 1 hour, thus the units is by default measured in hours.
localeLang - The locale language for date and time string. For example,  en or ja.
localeCountry - The locale country for date and time string. For example, US or JP. If localeLang is not specified, this input will be ingored.

Returns\:
The offset date/time. 

Responses\:
success - Operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.description=Ce flow permet d'attendre la fin de l'exécution d'un flow HPOO et de retourner le status final d'exécution ainsi que les outputs. Il permet de positionner un timeout plus étendu que celui proposé en standard par l'opération HPOO. Le flow prend en input l'ID d'exécution du flow dont il faut attendre la fin de traitement ainsi que le timeout (temps max d'attente de ce composant) et la fréquence de vériication du statut d'exécution. Exemple \: Si l'on spécifie \: - timeout \= 3600 (secondes) - checkFrequency \= 60 (secondes) Le composant vérifiera le statut d'exécution du flow toutes les 60 secondes. Cette boucle de vérification s'arretera lorsque le timeout spécifié sera atteint. Inputs\: -------------------------------- flowRunID \: (obligatoire) ID d'exécution du flow dont il faut attendre la fin timeout\: (obligatoire) Timeout global du composant en secondes checkFrequency\: (facultatif) Fréquence (en secondes) de vérification du statut d'exécution du flow pendant l'écoulement du timeout. Valeur par défaut 60 (secondes) Outputs\: -------------------------------- flowOutputs \: Outputs du flow (l'ensemble des "Flow Output Field" du flow appelé) flowResponse \: Réponse du flow appelé. Il s'agit du step final de sortie du flow appelé (Error, Resolved, Diagnosed, No Action Taken). En cas de plantage du flow appelé, la réponse "Failed" est renvoyée. flowExecutionStatus \: Status d'exécution du flow appelé. Ce composant peut renvoyer l'une des valeurs suivantes \: - Finished \: l'exécution du flow appelé est terminée - Unknown \: status d'exécution du flow appelé inconnu - Canceled \: le flow appelé a été volontairement annulé - Paused \: le flow appelé a été volontairement suspendu - Timeout \: le timeout positionné en entrée de ce composant s'est écoulé avant la fin de l'exécution du flow appelé - Error waiting for flow completion \: une erreur est survenue dans la boucle d'attente de la fin de l'exécution du flow appelé - Error getting execution status \: impossible de déterminer le status d'exécution du flow appelé Responses\: -------------------------------- Success \: L'exécution du flow appelé s'est terminé Diagnosed \: Détermination de l'exécution du flow appelé impossible (Timeout écoulé ou statut d'exécution inconnu ou boucle d'attente en erreur) Not Action Taken \: Le flow appelé a été volontairement annulé ou suspendu 56d19f65-ba7c-4acb-b89f-4cad969a6f03.ebe35160-cc88-4d9a-9f72-4a75298142b2.description=
